Parents who refuse to vaccinate their children must give up their childcare payments from the government unless care is quarantined to the home, according to a new report.

This hard-line approach to immunisation is part of the recommendations handed down by the Productivity Commission's report into childcare.

The report warns that access to government rebates for childcare should only be handed out if the child is fully immunised in order to protect them from preventable diseases.

